## Chart Line Colors for Indicators

Assign each indicator a permanent, never-changing color. Users will learn them:

```
EMA 10:   #2979ff   → Deep blue
EMA 20:   #aa00ff   → Violet
EMA 50:   #ff6d00   → Orange
EMA 200:  #f50057   → Hot pink (most important, most visible)
VWAP:     #ff9100   → Amber-orange (institutional benchmark)
ATR TR:   #ff1744   → Alert red (reversal signal)
CVD:      #00b0ff   → Sky blue
RSI:      #76ff03   → Chartreuse (sub-panel)
```

**Critical rule:** EMA200 should be the most visually prominent EMA because it's the most institutionally significant. The hot pink at 1.2px weight stands out clearly.

---

## Alert Lines on Chart

```
Alert line color:          #ffd700   → Gold (always gold, universally recognizable)
Position entry line:        #00d4a8 for long, #ff4d6a for short
Stop loss line:             #ff8c42   → Orange (distinct from SL order color for contrast)
Target line:                #00d4a8 dashed
```

